sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users) AS total_users,
  (SELECT AVG(price) FROM items) AS average_item_price;

external_knowledge:
- "Top 10 frequent shoppers" refers to users who have placed the most orders;
- "Favorite category" refers to the category of items that appears most frequently in their orders;
- "Shining the brightest" is a metaphor for having the highest number of orders and the highest average order value.

- "tallest trees" refers to items with the highest user behavior count;
- "forest dwellers" refers to users;
- "drawing the most attention" means the items have the highest number of user interactions.

- "frequent shoppers" refers to users who have placed more than two orders;
- "land of the free" refers to the USA;
- "delivered treasures" refers to items that have been delivered to the users.

- 'Top spenders' refers to users who have spent more than the average total amount on shipped and non-returned items.; 
- 'Shipped orders' are orders whose status is marked as shipped in the `orders` table.;
- 'Non-returned items' are items that have not been marked as returned in the `order_items` table.

- "stars of each category" refers to the top 3 most purchased items in each category;
- "shone the brightest" refers to the highest purchase counts;
- "chosen by shoppers" refers to the items that have been included in orders;
- "bustling market of items" is a metaphor for the database of items and their purchase records.

- 'Active users' refers to users whose `is_active` flag is set to 1;
- 'Active categories' refers to categories whose `is_active` flag is set to 1;
- 'Unique browsing events' refers to distinct entries in the `browsing_history` table.

- 'top-spending users' refers to users who have the highest total amount spent;
- 'delivered orders' are orders that have a status of 'delivered';
- 'more than two delivered orders' means the user has placed more than two orders that have been delivered.

- "total purchase amount" refers to the sum of the final prices of items purchased, multiplied by their quantities;
- "average total purchase amount of all users" is the mean of the total purchase amounts for all users;
- "most recent order" is the order with the latest `order_date` for each user.
